Interface TSPAlgorithm<V,E>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the graph vertex type
    E - the graph edge type
    All Superinterfaces:
    HamiltonianCycleAlgorithm<V,E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HeldKarpTSP, TwoApproxMetricTSP, TwoOptHeuristicTSP
    Deprecated. 
    interface replaced by HamiltonianCycleAlgorithm

    @Deprecated
public interface TSPAlgorithm<V,E>
extends HamiltonianCycleAlgorithm<V,E>
    An algorithm solving the Travelling salesman problem (TSP).

    Given a list of cities and the distances between each pair of cities, what is the shortest possible route that visits each city exactly once and returns to the origin city?

    Author:
    Dimitrios Michail
